  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B Marketing Administrator",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a dynamic, driven person to administer our brand and content. You will act as the glue behind our digital presence, working alongside our various venue team members, to always deliver compelling, authentic content.</p><p>This is more than just content creation—you’ll need to understand and relate to the brand, fully understand it to translate it into captivating content. You will also handle all aspects of marketing work across platforms, ensuring consistency and timeliness in every piece of work. This involves owning your administrative work.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><p>– Involved in all aspects of Marketing work, including ensuring timely content creation and posts, and coordination with venues on project tasks for events and activations.</p><p>– Oversee the planning, scheduling, and delivery of content across digital platforms.</p><p>– Manage and guide on all photography and videography, ensuring alignment with brand strategy and timely execution.</p><p>– Immerse yourself in the brand ethos and voice.</p><p>– Always stay informed on F&B and street culture trends to ensure our content remains fresh, bold, and culturally relevant.</p><p>– Monitor and adapt to performance analytics and trends to continuously optimize marketing and content output.</p><p>– Keep abreast of digital and social media innovations to bring cutting-edge ideas.<br /></p><p>- Manage all areas of marketing work, including communication and support at all venues plus collateral production and printing.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Qualifications and Skills</strong></p><p>– Good project management skills.<br /></p><p>- Strong administration background is a must.</p><p>– Ability to do photography, videography will be great.</p><p>– Skilled in copywriting. Good command of English.</p><p>– Proficiency in content creation and editing tools (e.g., Adobe Creative Suite, Canva, mobile editing apps).</p><p>– Collaborative spirit with excellent communication and organizational skills.</p><p>– A keen eye for detail and quality, balancing creativity with brand consistency.</p><p>– Familiarity with social media management and analytics tools (e.g., Meta Business, Google Analytics) will be useful.</p><p>– Understanding of engagement metrics and digital content performance.</p><p>- Fresh Graduates welcomed.</p><p>- Salary will commensurate with experience.</p>",
